				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${I}_{n}$$\end{document}, the bimetal only deflects without closing the clearance with the primary mechanism. Nevertheless, for the case 1.13×In\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1.13\times {I}_{n}$$\end{document}, the bimetal closes the gap with the switching mechanism but fails to reach the required tripping force. This is an excellent example of a design that complies with the requirements of the IEC 60898-1 standard.Figure 10
